ey have also produced some unintended legal implications for individuals and businesses, particularly in the areas of contractual obligations, employment relationships, tourism and hospitality, company law, competition law, human rights and the rule of law, protection of vulnerable groups like migrant workers, and access to judicial and legal services. COVID-19 and Business Law: Legal Implications of a Global Pandemic identifies and discusses specific legal challenges caused by the COVID-19 pandemic in these areas and suggests possible ways in which they could be remedied.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aCOVID-19. 4aGlobale Pandemie. 4aMenschenrechte. 4aRechtliche Implikationen. 4aRechtsstaatlichkeit. 4aWirtschaftsrecht. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Business Law.2bisacsh  aCovid-19 and Business Law, Global Pandemic, Legal Implications of COVID-19, Global Pandemic and Individuals and Businesses, Human Rights and the Rule of Law.1 aAli Mohamed, Ashgar Ali, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGan, Joo-Ee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarim, Ridoan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrishnan, Loganathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLatha Ramalingam, Chithra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMajid, Abdul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMydin Meera, Vazeer Alam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRachagan, Danusha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharma, Priya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSivakumaran, Sunitha S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThuraisingham